My neighbor is still employed at his Fred Flintstone type job where he literally stands in front of an outdoor conveyor belt line on which stones are carried that he has to break into smaller stones and sort out. It's so comforting to me that this type of work still exists today.

Imagine it. You drive down to the quarry in the early morning. You're out in the sun at the conveyer line and a rock is approaching. You hit it with a sledgehammer so it splits apart into multiple rocks and then order the pieces in a line (?) and wait for the next one to arrive.
